It'll be written in traditional third person (no second person this time around) though I'm keeping in the greentexts. It's easier for me to write like this in preparation for a second draft where I write in traditional pose. This new green is basically going to be a first draft for a potential novel. I'm confident that if I drafted Amaroq a few times and made it digestible for normies (no anthros obviously, standard first person much to my chagrin) I would have a chance at getting it published. >The Adventures of Andi of Oakenhowler

Jurassic fever, by anon.

“Subjects 2, 3, and 4, are currently attempting to breach the egg shell, however subject 1 is not displaying symptoms of hatching at this time awaiting further orders”

Avery grew concerned, he wiped his brow and spoke again.

“Scan subject one for vitals Debora”

“Yes sir scanning subject one for vital signs”

“Subject one vital signs normal, anomalies detected 1”

Avery shot up from his seat in a panic eyes wide as he stared at the monitor next to him that displayed a bright red number 1.

“Wh-what do you mean Debora, what anomaly are you talking about”

“Subject one is unable to breach egg shell due to genetic defect, scans indicate subject one has inherited a genetic defect that has prevented the growth of an egg tooth, suggested course of action...assistance in breaching egg shell”

Avery was out of his chair before “in breaching” even made it out. Tbc

This kinda goes with the idea that I was rolling around in my head, because the biggest “no” for a pokemon /hmofa/ story was not making them equals. Or more equal then they normally are from what i remember. Basically the training or ownership of pokemon was kinda out if they were on the same level of us, wanting them as equals and not pets.
When trying to figure out what would be a reason for them to partner with humans, I thought up of a kind of “superhero” universe. It’s basically the same thing pokemon rangers do, just using pokemon abilities to help or make life easier. This kinda goes along with the idea that humans focus or recharge their power, buffing like mentioned so it is stronger or takes less energy, and where pokemon not assisted by humans are almost out of control in power.
For example, why abra and it’s evolution is so expressionless and clam is because psychics are like raven from teen titans, emotions or energy just causes powers to flare up and destroy. But with a human, they could have more control and be expressive without worry.
